SIMPLE: wittol
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wittol
<hw>Wit"tol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Said to be for
<ets>white tail</ets>, and so called in allusion to its white tail; but
cf. <ets>witwal</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The wheatear.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A man who knows his wife's infidelity and submits to
it; a tame cuckold; -- so called because the cuckoo lays its eggs in the
wittol's nest.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wittolly</ent>⟦br⟧
